{"id":274890,"name":null,"username":"xesf","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/xesf/{size}/122_2.png","created_at":"2007-01-07T13:21:00.000Z","cooked":"<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"El_Muerte\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"8818\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n El_Muerte:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>cool does this version also work with a multi monitor setup?</p>\n<p>Feature request:<br>\n- ability to make panorama shots <img src=\"https://forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, I think. If you want I can test later night.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I know this is an old thread, but I think I have a valid question.<br>\nThe export to Maya, it comes up saying Export impossible, this is not a maya build.<br>\nAny chance of a workaround or an update?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Maybe not, Yaz0r release it without this option with his own in intentions I think. He already got some problems with other projects he have by making such export options.</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T19:53:23.363Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":5.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":8818,"topic_slug":"lba2-exterior-viewer-v0-1","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"raw":"\n[quote=\"El_Muerte,post:8,topic:8818\"]\ncool... does this version also work with a multi monitor setup?\n\nFeature request:\n\\-